        {
            "date": "2009-07-29 11:15:20", 
            "sentences": [
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": true, 
                    "text": "I am not requiring Dan to write a test, but I am requiring that a fix for this\nproblem have a test.", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": true
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "  The message display code, especially given the current\nmultiplexed tab implementation, is not simple.", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "  Given that complexity, untested\ncode is likely to break again.", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": true, 
                    "text": "  My position is that it's better to leave it\nbroken until properly fixed (which means with a test) rather than apply a fix\nthat removes the motivation for someone else to fix it with a test.", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": true
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "  Also,\nmaking changes to an unconstrained (by tests) feature is likely to have other\nside effects that may be worse.\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "If the affected code were not something that is intimately related to already\nwell-tested code with an already-existing test framework, I would be less of a\nhard-ass about this.\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }
            ], 
